00:28:22.290 --> 00:28:24.840
But, because they're
constantly moving and growing,

00:28:24.840 --> 00:28:28.290
that's not been an issue for me.

00:28:28.290 --> 00:28:30.407
I do, when they want
stuff that's crap,

00:28:30.407 --> 00:28:32.740
you know, they see other kids
having stuff that's crap--

00:28:32.740 --> 00:28:34.160
like, they eat sugar.

00:28:34.160 --> 00:28:34.920
They eat fat.

00:28:34.920 --> 00:28:38.220
Like, I put organic
Cheetos in their lunch.

00:28:38.220 --> 00:28:39.957
Luke's makes an organic Cheeto.

00:28:39.957 --> 00:28:41.040
Like, I put that in there.

00:28:41.040 --> 00:28:42.956
Or I'll-- you know, every
day they get a treat

00:28:42.956 --> 00:28:45.450
in their lunch, but I'll put
like an organic peanut butter

00:28:45.450 --> 00:28:48.956
cup from Justin's, or a little
OCHO chocolate caramel bar

00:28:48.956 --> 00:28:50.330
that's organic,
because I'm like,

00:28:50.330 --> 00:28:51.980
they'll burn the sugar off.

00:28:51.980 --> 00:28:54.632
But their little bodies
cannot handle the chemicals.

00:28:54.632 --> 00:28:56.340
Their organs aren't
