I don't have kids, but inspiring
your spouse to, you know,

00:29:52.990 --> 00:29:56.350
get in shape and stay in
shape, without ever making them

00:29:56.350 --> 00:30:00.646
feel like they need
to or et cetera.

00:30:00.646 --> 00:30:04.850
JILLIAN MICHAELS: [EXHALES]
It depends on the spouse.

00:30:04.850 --> 00:30:10.370
There are two strategies you
can employ to motivate someone.

00:30:10.370 --> 00:30:12.160
The first is you
lead by example.

00:30:12.160 --> 00:30:15.530
And, in truth, it's
really all you have.

00:30:15.530 --> 00:30:16.800
You lead by example.

00:30:16.800 --> 00:30:19.280
You talk about the things
that you want and perspective

00:30:19.280 --> 00:30:21.770
on the outcome, you
know, what's the why.

00:30:21.770 --> 00:30:24.650
If you have a why to live
for, you can tolerate the how.

00:30:24.650 --> 00:30:25.550
What's your why?

00:30:25.550 --> 00:30:27.230
How do you see the future?

00:30:27.230 --> 00:30:30.740
Very innocently asking
them what their why is,

00:30:30.740 --> 00:30:32.390
what they see for the future.

00:30:32.390 --> 00:30:36.029
Letting them be motivated
and inspired by your journey.

00:30:36.029 --> 00:30:36.820
Sometimes it works.

00:30:36.820 --> 00:30:38.500
Sometimes it doesn't.

00:30:38.500 --> 00:30:41.110
The other thing is to
just literally crack them

00:30:41.110 --> 00:30:43.630
over the head with
fear and concern.

00:30:43.630 --> 00:30:45.400
And sometimes it works.

00:30:45.400 --> 00:30:46.540
Sometimes it doesn't.

00:30:46.540 --> 00:30:50.110
And the reality is that people--

00:30:50.110 --> 00:30:52.970
remember that whatever
the food or the behavior

00:30:52.970 --> 00:30:56.050
is providing them, it's
something significant for them.

00:30:56.050 --> 00:30:57.400
They may not even understand it.

00:30:57.400 --> 00:30:58.774
You might not even
understand it.

00:30:58.774 --> 00:31:02.230
But it has to hurt
more to continue

00:31:02.230 --> 00:31:05.020
the way they've been living
than the work and the fear

00:31:05.020 --> 00:31:08.660
and the loss associated with
where you want them to go.

00:31:08.660 --> 00:31:10.544
And that's where if
they see you being like,

00:31:10.544 --> 00:31:12.460
I'm afraid you're going
to have a heart attack

00:31:12.460 --> 00:31:15.079
and orphan our two
kids, I really am,

00:31:15.079 --> 00:31:16.120
and you're just in tears.

00:31:16.120 --> 00:31:18.453
And it's not, you're an
asshole, you're lazy, it's like,

00:31:18.453 --> 00:31:20.290
listen, I love you.

00:31:20.290 --> 00:31:21.340
I'm really afraid.

00:31:21.340 --> 00:31:23.710
This is a reality I
think we're facing.

00:31:23.710 --> 00:31:29.230
And if you can hurt them enough,
make them feel-- or you're not

00:31:29.230 --> 00:31:32.530
hurting them, but make
them feel the hurt of that,

00:31:32.530 --> 00:31:34.660
and it's more
uncomfortable where

00:31:34.660 --> 00:31:38.322
they are than where
they need to go,

00:31:38.322 --> 00:31:40.030
you've got another
chance of them moving.

00:31:40.030 --> 00:31:42.580
But sometimes that
stuff is so deep.

00:31:42.580 --> 00:31:45.200
And I can give you one example
of what I'm talking about.

00:31:45.200 --> 00:31:47.987
So-- I can give you
many, but here's one.

00:31:47.987 --> 00:31:50.320
So there was a kid that I
worked with on "Biggest Loser"

00:31:50.320 --> 00:31:52.900
for a little while, and he was
doing great, he was like 18,

00:31:52.900 --> 00:31:55.990
he was there with his dad,
they were both doing great.

00:31:55.990 --> 00:31:58.870
They went home for the
holidays, and they all

00:31:58.870 --> 00:32:02.560
come back to the "Biggest Loser"
ranch, everybody's weighing in,

00:32:02.560 --> 00:32:04.170
and it's like
everyone's doing great,

00:32:04.170 --> 00:32:06.835
and the dad gets on the
scale, he lost nothing.

00:32:06.835 --> 00:32:08.260
And the room gets kind of quiet.

00:32:08.260 --> 00:32:10.676
The kid gets on the scale, and
he gained like five pounds.

00:32:10.676 --> 00:32:12.350
They were gone for two weeks.

00:32:12.350 --> 00:32:14.605
And everyone starts with
the bullshit of like, oh,

00:32:14.605 --> 00:32:16.780
the traveling, and the
food at the airport,

00:32:16.780 --> 00:32:17.950
and the whole-- they start.

00:32:17.950 --> 00:32:19.658
And that--you know
that's not what it is.

00:32:19.658 --> 00:32:23.760
So I'm like, listen, just tell
me what happened step by step.

00:32:23.760 --> 00:32:25.455
So he starts with
the, I packed my lunch

00:32:25.455 --> 00:32:28.380
and, you know, with
the surface stuff,

00:32:28.380 --> 00:32:30.750
and I go to the airport,
and this, that, the other,

00:32:30.750 --> 00:32:33.390
and I walk in the door, and
all my friends and family

00:32:33.390 --> 00:32:37.050
are there, and there's my mom,
and she starts crying and not

00:32:37.050 --> 00:32:38.550
tears of joy.

00:32:38.550 --> 00:32:42.780
So it turns out that mom is
morbidly obese, and upon seeing

00:32:42.780 --> 00:32:45.780
husband and son being
significantly more fit,

00:32:45.780 --> 00:32:49.380
I mean, she immediately
shuts down, withdraws,

00:32:49.380 --> 00:32:52.170
becomes depressed, feels like
they're going to abandon her,

00:32:52.170 --> 00:32:54.780
like, they've outgrown her,
they've left her behind.

00:32:54.780 --> 00:32:57.045
And so, you know, it's the
primal abandonment for him,

00:32:57.045 --> 00:32:57.878
and what does he do?

00:32:57.878 --> 00:33:00.297
He slams the brakes on the
weight loss and starts eating.

00:33:00.297 --> 00:33:01.630
What does the weight afford him?

00:33:01.630 --> 00:33:03.979
An emotional connection
with his mother.

00:33:03.979 --> 00:33:05.520
You think you can
change that easily?

00:33:05.520 --> 00:33:07.125
AUDIENCE: No.

00:33:07.125 --> 00:33:09.420
JILLIAN MICHAELS: No way.

00:33:09.420 --> 00:33:12.360
So, you've got to appreciate
that you may never

00:33:12.360 --> 00:33:14.730
know what the answer is, or
why they're attached to it.

00:33:14.730 --> 00:33:16.230
They may never know.

00:33:16.230 --> 00:33:18.990
But it has nothing
to do with you.

00:33:18.990 --> 00:33:21.240
Those two strategies may work.

00:33:21.240 --> 00:33:21.782
They may not.

00:33:21.782 --> 00:33:23.448
You'll hear a lot of
people say, well, I

00:33:23.448 --> 00:33:26.160
had a massive heart attack
and then I changed my ways.

00:33:26.160 --> 00:33:27.420
Look at Clinton.

00:33:27.420 --> 00:33:30.490
Massive heart attack, and
then he changed his ways,

00:33:30.490 --> 00:33:32.490
but that's what it took.

00:33:32.490 --> 00:33:35.130
I hope that doesn't happen, but
sometimes a rock bottom moment

00:33:35.130 --> 00:33:37.926
is necessary, and you
can't facilitate that.

00:33:37.926 --> 00:33:39.260
MARY LIZ MCCURDY: Thanks.

