bit more complicated, like,

00:33:57.770 --> 00:33:59.690
if you want to lose
weight, gain muscle,

00:33:59.690 --> 00:34:02.570
and how do you go about that
with nutrition wise, what

00:34:02.570 --> 00:34:05.120
to eat, when and what
time, after a workout,

00:34:05.120 --> 00:34:08.110
before a workout, and, like--
and if you're going to, like,

00:34:08.110 --> 00:34:10.520
lose the weight, are you
going to, like, sprint 5K,

00:34:10.520 --> 00:34:13.350
or are you just going to do
like a long-- like, you know,

00:34:13.350 --> 00:34:14.864
just sprint just
short distances?

00:34:14.864 --> 00:34:15.739
You know what I mean?

00:34:15.739 --> 00:34:16.614
JILLIAN MICHAELS: OK.

00:34:16.614 --> 00:34:17.456
AUDIENCE: So like--

00:34:17.456 --> 00:34:19.190
I'm sorry.

00:34:19.190 --> 00:34:20.884
I've always wanted
to ask you that.

00:34:20.884 --> 00:34:22.050
JILLIAN MICHAELS: All right.

00:34:22.050 --> 00:34:27.260
So, first of all, women don't
really gain muscle size.

00:34:27.260 --> 00:34:29.134
It's really hard.

00:34:29.134 --> 00:34:30.400
I mean, you could.

00:34:30.400 --> 00:34:35.360
You'd have to eat a lot of
food and lift very heavy,

00:34:35.360 --> 00:34:39.020
and really be extraordinarily
diligent about that.

00:34:39.020 --> 00:34:43.010
We just don't have the
androgenic hormones to like--

00:34:43.010 --> 00:34:44.389
we can maintain muscle.

00:34:44.389 --> 00:34:46.190
We can burn intramuscular fat.

00:34:46.190 --> 00:34:47.420
We can condition muscle.

00:34:47.420 --> 00:34:50.360
But to like literally make
something bigger on your body

00:34:50.360 --> 00:34:52.739
by adding muscle,
it's very hard to do.

00:34:52.739 --> 00:34:55.932
Like, Mr. Olympia puts on
three pounds of muscle a year.

00:34:55.932 --> 00:34:57.890
When you think, like,
God, is that all, I mean,

00:34:57.890 --> 00:34:59.180
if you take three
pounds of hamburger meat

00:34:59.180 --> 00:35:01.554
and slap it on your body, it's
a hell of a lot of muscle.

00:35:01.554 --> 00:35:03.320
But, at the same
time, like, when

00:35:03.320 --> 00:35:04.825
you put it in perspective--

00:35:04.825 --> 00:35:06.200
because trainers
are like, oh no,

00:35:06.200 --> 00:35:07.130
you're just--you know
what you're doing?

00:35:07.130 --> 00:35:07.910
You're gaining muscle.

00:35:07.910 --> 00:35:08.690
That's bullshit.

00:35:08.690 --> 00:35:12.440
So it's not that you've offset
loss with muscle gain; that's

00:35:12.440 --> 00:35:14.497
not true.

00:35:14.497 --> 00:35:16.580
So you've really got to
focus on one or the other.

00:35:16.580 --> 00:35:19.310
If you want to gain size,
which I don't think that's

00:35:19.310 --> 00:35:20.210
what you mean.

00:35:20.210 --> 00:35:23.270
But you can't gain and
drop at the same time.

00:35:23.270 --> 00:35:25.640
So-- and fat does
not turn into muscle.

00:35:25.640 --> 00:35:26.900
It's not led into gold.

00:35:26.900 --> 00:35:30.800
So you would drop the weight and
then start putting on muscle.

00:35:30.800 --> 00:35:34.010
With that said, if you're
like I just want to get leaner

00:35:34.010 --> 00:35:36.191
and I want to lower my
body fat, which is what

00:35:36.191 --> 00:35:37.440
it sounds like you want to do.

00:35:37.440 --> 00:35:38.180
AUDIENCE: Yeah, probably.

00:35:38.180 --> 00:35:40.846
JILLIAN MICHAELS: Condition your
muscle and lower your body fat,

00:35:40.846 --> 00:35:43.430
it doesn't matter what you do,
as long as you're consistent.

00:35:43.430 --> 00:35:47.000
What will get you there faster,
sure, high-intensity training

00:35:47.000 --> 00:35:49.220
for shorter periods of time.

00:35:49.220 --> 00:35:51.380
20 to 30 minutes,
four to five times

00:35:51.380 --> 00:35:54.230
a week, with-- in
conjunction with being

00:35:54.230 --> 00:35:57.770
really good about your diet,
will get you there the fastest.

00:35:57.770 --> 00:36:00.150
And if you take a
duration-- a long duration,

00:36:00.150 --> 00:36:03.410
low-intensity day, make it like
your off day or your recovery

00:36:03.410 --> 00:36:04.940
day, that'll get you there.

00:36:04.940 --> 00:36:07.820
Just take you longer
because it won't

00:36:07.820 --> 00:36:11.310
affect your metabolism
as intensely,

00:36:11.310 --> 00:36:13.200
or your EPOC, your afterburn.

00:36:13.200 --> 00:36:15.510
Your elevated
metabolic rate is not

00:36:15.510 --> 00:36:18.280
as great from lower
intensity exercise.

00:36:18.280 --> 00:36:22.320
So, high intensity gives
you a greater burn during,

00:36:22.320 --> 00:36:24.570
greater burn after
the workout's over.

00:36:24.570 --> 00:36:30.760
It-- oh God-- it facilitates
improved fitness faster,

00:36:30.760 --> 00:36:33.120
which allows-- continues to
allow for greater intensity,

00:36:33.120 --> 00:36:35.560
and it becomes--

00:36:35.560 --> 00:36:38.790
it gains momentum, and you work
out harder, you get fitter,

00:36:38.790 --> 00:36:40.010
you work out--

00:36:40.010 --> 00:36:40.590
holy shit.

00:36:40.590 --> 00:36:41.797
Forgive me.

00:36:41.797 --> 00:36:43.380
You work out harder,
you get more fit,

00:36:43.380 --> 00:36:45.700
you burn more calories, and
the cycle begets itself,

00:36:45.700 --> 00:36:46.630
if that makes sense.

00:36:46.630 --> 00:36:46.680
AUDIENCE: Yeah.

00:36:46.680 --> 00:36:47.130
JILLIAN MICHAELS:
But there's not

00:36:47.130 --> 00:36:48.551
going to be a
right or wrong way.

00:36:48.551 --> 00:36:50.550
There's just going to be
a faster or slower way.

00:36:50.550 --> 00:36:53.120
AUDIENCE: What about the eating
wise, like, what to eat and all

00:36:53.120 --> 00:36:53.805
that, and like to--

00:36:53.805 --> 00:36:56.304
JILLIAN MICHAELS: If you want
to-- what do you want to lose?

00:36:56.304 --> 00:36:59.172
AUDIENCE: Like 15 pounds
or something, and also

00:36:59.172 --> 00:36:59.880
gain the weight--

00:36:59.880 --> 00:37:01.005
JILLIAN MICHAELS: With 15--

00:37:01.005 --> 00:37:04.350
but I would say, you know, if
you're in that vanity pound

00:37:04.350 --> 00:37:07.680
range, don't create more
of a calorie deficit

00:37:07.680 --> 00:37:08.750
than 500 calories.

00:37:08.750 --> 00:37:11.930
Because I bet if I took you
to the doctor right now,

00:37:11.930 --> 00:37:13.890
you would-- your blood
pressure would be good,

00:37:13.890 --> 00:37:16.020
your heart rate would be
good, your fasting glucose

00:37:16.020 --> 00:37:17.936
would be good, your
cholesterol would be good,

00:37:17.936 --> 00:37:20.700
and your body is like,
well, I'm perfectly healthy,

00:37:20.700 --> 00:37:22.650
why is she starving me?

00:37:22.650 --> 00:37:26.370
And so it would signal a
metabolic shift to slow down.

00:37:26.370 --> 00:37:28.110
Because that's
what metabolism is.

00:37:28.110 --> 00:37:29.820
It's biochemistry.

00:37:29.820 --> 00:37:32.830
It's the hormone balance
of human growth hormone,

00:37:32.830 --> 00:37:36.030
insulin, cortisol, grow and
let-- all of those things work

00:37:36.030 --> 00:37:39.240
in a symphony, and
they are all responding

00:37:39.240 --> 00:37:43.530
to your environments and
your food, your stress levels

00:37:43.530 --> 00:37:44.160
and so on.

00:37:44.160 --> 00:37:47.820
So if you are reducing
your calories too much

00:37:47.820 --> 00:37:49.530
and you're already
fit and healthy,

00:37:49.530 --> 00:37:51.919
your body is going to signal
metabolic slow shutdown.

00:37:51.919 --> 00:37:53.460
So that's where with
people like you,

00:37:53.460 --> 00:37:57.420
I'm like go to no more
than a 500-calorie deficit,

00:37:57.420 --> 00:37:58.630
and eat clean.

00:37:58.630 --> 00:38:00.880
So, if you're using your
little contraption that says,

00:38:00.880 --> 00:38:05.190
hey, you burned
2000 calories today,

00:38:05.190 --> 00:38:11.330
and you eat 1,500, that's really
kind of where you want to be.

00:38:11.330 --> 00:38:12.330
And don't eat chemicals.

00:38:12.330 --> 00:38:13.320
Keep it simple.

00:38:13.320 --> 00:38:15.049
Doesn't need to be--

00:38:15.049 --> 00:38:15.840
don't overthink it.

00:38:15.840 --> 00:38:18.762
When you overthink it,
it's impossible to sustain.

00:38:18.762 --> 00:38:22.270
Just because something is
simple doesn't mean it's easy,

00:38:22.270 --> 00:38:24.570
but at least if you
can stick with it,

00:38:24.570 --> 00:38:27.000
it's a heck of a lot more
accessible than too much

00:38:27.000 --> 00:38:28.803
information and all of that.

